<br>
On the good point, here's a story. Couple weeks ago I was in DN fighting phase spiders. I tried to use my epic pet on them, but the spiders would always displace the epic before they displaced the tank (and the pet had a hell of a time finding his way back after a displacement) (NOT attack the pet. Never once did the spider turn away from the tank to bash a pet. Once upon a time they made the phase spider power as a proc..., now it goes to whomever has the highest aggro). So I brought out rocky the earth pet. Rocky has crappy crappy armor class, less hit points then skittles, generally lower level and still does about 80% of the meele damage of skittles. But rocky only casts a root... He does NOT proc a 140 pt dd every 6 seconds and a stun every 12 seconds. Rocky never once got displaced before the tank... enchanter... cleric... wizard... The epic's super implicit taunt all comes from the proc and the stun, not his &quot;low&quot; ac or low level.<br>
<br>
If warriors tossed 140 point dds and stuns like clockwork, they too will outtaunt skittles. In fact, that's exactly what paladins do (group heals and stuns)... during the period when pets could hold aggro, a paladin using his spells appropriately could easily outtaunt skittles. <p>Cydmab Promethean, Triune <BR>
Level 59 Conjurer, Morell Thule <BR>
